Music use Questionnaire (Chin & Rickard 2012)

Index of Music Listening 
IML1        On average, how often do you listen to music a week 
IML2        On average, how many hours do you purposefully listen to music a day 

Instructions	Using the scale provided as a guide, indicate how much you agree or disagree with each of the following statements by selecting the corresponding number

Scoring:	  1: Strongly disagree 
	          2: Disagree 
	          3: Neutral 
	          4: Agree
	          5: Strongly Agree 
MES I (Cognitive and Emotion Regulation) 

MESI1	      I often listen to music when I'm feeling down 
MESI2	      Specific types of music make me feel better
MESI3	      Music often takes away tension at the end of the day 
MESI4	      I often listen to new compositions 
MESI5	      I use a particular type of music to get me through tough times 
MESI6	      Music is often a source of inspiration for me 
MESI7	      Certain types of music help me think 

R CODE 
Cognitive and Emotion Regulation 
mydata$MESI <- (mydata$MESI1 + mydata$MESI2 + mydata$MESI3 + mydata$MESI4 + mydata$MESI5 + mydata$MESI6 + mydata$MESI7)

MES III (Social connection)

MESIII1	    Having a similar taste in mysic often helps me relate better to my peers
MESIII2	    I am able to make more friends when we like the same type of music 
MESIII3	    There is a greater connection with my friends when we like the same music 

R CODE 
Social Connection 
mydata$MESIII <- (mydata$MESIII1 + mydata$MESIII2 + mydata$MESIII3)
